  "page": 42,
  "spans": [
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0001",
      "text": "INCITS xxx-200x Link Services Rev 1.61 November 3, 2006",
      "bbox": [
        301.08,
        37.27,
        539.95,
        47.32
      ],
      "block_index": 1,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0002",
      "text": " 23",
      "bbox": [
        521.04,
        723.59,
        534.92,
        734.7
      ],
      "block_index": 2,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0003",
      "text": "The following rules regarding Sequence and Exchange management apply to ELSs in addition to the",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        57.65,
        539.82,
        68.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0004",
      "text": "rules specified in FC-FS-2:",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        69.65,
        214.21,
        80.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0005",
      "text": "a) Request and Reply Sequences may be sent in any class of service;",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        94.97,
        420.59,
        106.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0006",
      "text": "NOTE 2 – Not all of the classes make sense for all ELSs, but there is no restriction.",
      "bbox": [
        105.0,
        119.17,
        435.71,
        129.22
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0007",
      "text": "b) Reply frames and Sequences shall be transmitted in the same class as the request;",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        142.97,
        491.85,
        154.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0008",
      "text": "c)",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        166.97,
        114.34,
        178.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0009",
      "text": "If Login has not been completed successfully, the default Login values shall be used;",
      "bbox": [
        122.36,
        166.97,
        496.77,
        178.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0010",
      "text": "d) If Login has completed successfully, the Originator of the Exchange shall use the Discard mul-",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        190.97,
        540.06,
        202.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0011",
      "text": "tiple Sequences Error Policy for all ELS Exchanges (see FC-FS-2);",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        202.97,
        418.44,
        214.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0012",
      "text": "e) The Originator of an ELS Exchange shall detect an Exchange error following Sequence Initia-",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        226.96,
        540.05,
        238.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0013",
      "text": "tive transfer if the Reply Sequence is not received within a timeout interval of 2 X R_A_TOV;",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        238.96,
        529.08,
        250.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0014",
      "text": "f)",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        262.96,
        112.13,
        274.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0015",
      "text": "If the Exchange Originator of an ELS Exchange detects an Exchange error, it shall abort the",
      "bbox": [
        122.38,
        262.96,
        540.02,
        274.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0016",
      "text": "Exchange using ABTS-LS and retry the protocol of the aborted Exchange with a different Ex-",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        274.96,
        539.93,
        286.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0017",
      "text": "change;",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        286.96,
        157.93,
        298.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0018",
      "text": "g) If the Sequence Initiator aborts a Sequence using ABTS due to receiving an ACK with the",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        310.96,
        539.99,
        322.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0019",
      "text": "Abort Sequence bits set to 01b, the Sequence Initiator shall retry the Sequence after the",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        322.96,
        539.85,
        334.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0020",
      "text": "BA_ACC is received for the aborted Sequence one time only. If the retry fails, the ELS Ex-",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        334.96,
        540.21,
        346.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0021",
      "text": "change shall be aborted using ABTS-LS;",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        346.96,
        302.98,
        358.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0022",
      "text": "h) If the Sequence Initiator attempts to abort a Sequence using ABTS and it detects an E_D_TOV",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        370.96,
        540.04,
        382.08
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0023",
      "text": "waiting for the ACK frame in response to the ABTS, it shall abort the Exchange using ABTS-",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        382.96,
        540.05,
        394.08
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0024",
      "text": "LS, if conditions permit, and retry the original ELS with a different Exchange; and",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        394.96,
        479.04,
        406.08
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0025",
      "text": "i)",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        418.96,
        111.58,
        430.08
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0026",
      "text": "If the Sequence Initiator attempts to abort a Sequence using ABTS-LS and it detects an",
      "bbox": [
        122.42,
        418.96,
        540.02,
        430.08
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0027",
      "text": "E_D_TOV waiting for the ACK frame in response to the ABTS-LS, it may retry the original ELS",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        430.96,
        540.06,
        442.08
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0028",
      "text": "with a different Exchange.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        442.96,
        237.4,
        454.08
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0029",
      "text": "4.2.3",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        466.96,
        118.27,
        478.08
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0030",
      "text": "Advise Credit (ADVC)",
      "bbox": [
        128.27,
        466.96,
        230.29,
        478.08
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0031",
      "text": "4.2.3.1  Description",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        490.96,
        187.03,
        502.08
      ],
      "block_index": 15,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0032",
      "text": "The ADVC ELS is used to advise the destination Nx_Port of the estimated end-to-end Credit that the",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        514.96,
        540.04,
        526.08
      ],
      "block_index": 16,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0033",
      "text": "source Nx_Port requests to be allocated.  The ADVC ELS request shall be a separate Sequence.  It",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        526.96,
        540.05,
        538.08
      ],
      "block_index": 16,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0034",
      "text": "may also be requested in a separate Exchange.  See FC-FS-2 for the usage of this ELS.  The ADVC",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        538.96,
        539.94,
        550.08
      ],
      "block_index": 16,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0035",
      "text": "request may also be used independently from the Estimate Credit procedure (see FC-FS-2).",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        550.96,
        503.24,
        562.08
      ],
      "block_index": 16,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0036",
      "text": "4.2.3.2  Protocol",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        574.96,
        172.61,
        586.07
      ],
      "block_index": 17,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0037",
      "text": "a) Advise Credit Request Sequence",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        598.96,
        269.6,
        610.07
      ],
      "block_index": 18,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0038",
      "text": "b) LS_ACC or LS_RJT Reply Sequence",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        622.96,
        287.89,
        634.07
      ],
      "block_index": 19,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0039",
      "text": "4.2.3.3  Request Sequence",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        647.02,
        221.55,
        658.13
      ],
      "block_index": 20,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0040",
      "text": "Addressing: ",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        671.02,
        157.1,
        682.13
      ],
      "block_index": 21,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0041",
      "text": "The S_ID field designates the source Nx_Port requesting Credit revision.  The D_ID",
      "bbox": [
        157.08,
        671.02,
        540.02,
        682.13
      ],
      "block_index": 21,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 2
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p042_s0042",
      "text": "field designates the destination Nx_Port.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        683.02,
        274.86,
        694.13
      ],
      "block_index": 21,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    }
  ],
  "asset_ids": []
}